Redescription . Male . Body length 3.0– 4.5 mm , dark brownish grey, covered with silvery grey tomentum. Antenna dark brown to black; postpedicel pyriform with apex narrowly produced towards stylus (
Fig. 7
). Legs brown to greyish brown. Wing hyaline with brownish veins. Halter brownish white. Terminalia (Figs 11, 13– 16 ): hypandrium with long hook-shaped apical rods arising above base of long dorsally directed median apical process; postgonite projected dorsally as wide rounded lobe; phallus tubular, apex partially desclerotized and broadly expanded; epandrial lobe large with bifid dorsal process and rounded apex, apical surface covered with minute setulae; ventral subepandrial lobe lengthened with broad deflexed apex; medial subepandrial lobe wide, connected basally to both ventral subepandrial lobe and cercus, with short spine-like setulae along apical margin; cercus elongate, rounded apically with pronounced ventral hook.

Geographical distribution and seasonal occurrence (
Fig. 22
). Known from the montane and coastal forests of western North America from British Columbia , Washington and Oregon, south to northern California. Adults have been collected from the end of May until the middle of August.
